CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 14, 1963, pg. 8 reads: "Homewood-Brushton Civic Club was entertained, charmingly, at a Christmas party, by the president, Mrs. Gilbert (Carmen) Boddy, in handsomely decorated Boddy home, Mulford St. Shown are club members, seated (left to right): Mmes. Ollie Royal, Mary Walker, Carmen Boddy, the hostess; Ollie Finney and Larue Johnson.  Standing: Mmes. Rosalee Johnson, Mary Nesbit, Romaine Moore, Rachel Swain, Susan McCoy, Sophronia Collington, Maud Marshall, Esther Hodges and Georgia Paylor. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Homewood-Brushton Civic Club members, seated from left: Ollie Royal, Mary Walker, Carmen Boddy, Ollie Finney, and Larue Johnson; standing: Rosalee Johnson, Mary Nesbit, Romaine Moore, Rachel Swain, Susan McCoy, Sophronia Collington, Maud Marshall, Esther Hodges, and Georgia Paylor, gathered in home of Carmen Boddy for Christmas party, Mulford Street
